Package grafioschtrader.service

Class GTNetHistoryquoteService

java.lang.Object
grafioschtrader.service.BaseGTNetExchangeService
grafioschtrader.service.GTNetHistoryquoteService
@Service public class GTNetHistoryquoteService extends BaseGTNetExchangeService
Service for orchestrating historical price exchange with GTNet providers. This service implements bidirectional consumer and supplier flows for historical price sharing:

Consumer Side Flow (requesting data from remote servers)

  1. Build request with instruments and date ranges (fromDate = most recent local data + 1 day)
  2. Query push-open servers first (prioritized by consumerUsage)
  3. Query open servers for remaining unfilled instruments
  4. Store received data: local historyquote for local instruments, gt_net_historyquote for foreign
  5. Track "want to receive" responses from suppliers
  6. Push local historical data back to interested suppliers

"Want to Receive" Mechanism

When AC_OPEN suppliers cannot provide data but are configured to receive it, they return "want to receive" markers with the date from which they need data. This consumer then pushes local historical data back to those suppliers.

Storage Decision

When storing received historical quotes:
  • If instrument exists locally (GTNetInstrument.idSecuritycurrency != null): store in historyquote table
  • If instrument is foreign (GTNetInstrument.idSecuritycurrency == null): store in gt_net_historyquote table

    • requestHistoryquotesFromBaseThru

      public <S extends Securitycurrency<S>> HistoryquoteExchangeResult<S> requestHistoryquotesFromBaseThru(List<SecurityCurrencyMaxHistoryquoteData<S>> historySecurityCurrencyList, Calendar untilCalendar)
      Main integration point for BaseHistoryquoteThru. This method filters the input list by gtNetHistoricalRecv flag, queries GTNet servers in priority order, and returns a result indicating which instruments were filled and which need connector fallback. Also tracks "want to receive" markers for later push-back of connector-fetched data.
      Type Parameters:
      S - Security or Currencypair
      Parameters:
      historySecurityCurrencyList - the list of instruments from BaseHistoryquoteThru requiring updates
      untilCalendar - the target end date for historyquote loading
      Returns:
      result containing unfilled instruments, filled instruments, and want-to-receive map
